---
// Crude "what to expect tonight" sky visual. The canvas is drawn by the page
// client script (see index.astro) using the core track for the selected night.
---
<section class="card">
  <h2>Sky at best time — Milky Way band</h2>
  <canvas id="sky-canvas" width="900" height="460" role="img"
    aria-label="Diagram of the Milky Way band arching across the sky, looking south"></canvas>
  <div class="legend">
    <span><span class="swatch" style="background:#e6dcff"></span>Galactic core (brightest)</span>
    <span><span class="swatch" style="background:#96a0dc"></span>Milky Way band</span>
    <span><span class="swatch" style="background:#334;"></span>Horizon haze zone (&lt;10&deg;)</span>
    <span>View looks toward the horizon; up = higher in the sky.</span>
  </div>
</section>
